# Phase System for Apartment Blueprint Editor

## Context

The editor currently has no concept of construction/design phases. All building elements render unconditionally. This plan adds a phase system so objects can be assigned to phases (e.g., "Demolition", "New Construction", "Finishes") and filtered by three viewing modes. Phases are project-level, user-assignable, and view-only filters — they never alter actual model data.

---

## 1. Domain Model — New Files

### `src/domain/phaseModels.js` (NEW)

```js
createPhase(name, order, color)  → { id, name, order, color, visible: true }
createDefaultPhase()             → createPhase('Base Design', 0, '#4A90D9')
sortPhases(phases)               → sorted by order ascending
getOrderedPhases(project)        → sortPhases(project.phases || [])
getNextPhaseOrder(phases)        → max(order) + 1
reorderPhases(phases, movedId, newOrder) → re-indexes all order values
PHASE_COLORS = ['#4A90D9', '#E07B39', '#5BAE5B', '#C75D8E', '#8B6EC1', '#D4A843', '#44B4B4', '#D05555']
```

Uses `generateId('phase')` from `src/domain/ids.js`.

### `src/domain/phaseFilter.js` (NEW)

Pure functions — no React dependencies. Single source of truth for filtering.

```js
PHASE_VIEW = { ALL: 'all', SINGLE: 'single', CUMULATIVE: 'cumulative' }

filterFloorByPhase(floor, phases, activePhaseId, phaseViewMode)
  → returns shallow-copy floor with filtered arrays
  → ALL mode: returns floor unchanged
  → SINGLE mode: keeps objects where phaseId === activePhaseId or phaseId is null
  → CUMULATIVE mode: keeps objects where phase.order <= activePhase.order or phaseId is null
  → Also filters doors/windows whose parent wall was filtered out

isObjectVisibleInPhase(obj, phases, activePhaseId, phaseViewMode)
  → returns boolean for a single object

filterProjectByPhase(project, activePhaseId, phaseViewMode)
  → returns project with all floors filtered (for 3D/elevation/section)
```

Objects with `phaseId === null` (unassigned) are **always visible** in all modes.

### `src/hooks/usePhaseFilteredFloor.js` (NEW)

```js
usePhaseFilteredFloor(floor, project, activePhaseId, phaseViewMode)
  → useMemo wrapping filterFloorByPhase
```

