## 3. State Management

### `src/app/ProjectProvider.jsx`
New reducer actions:

| Action | Behavior |
|--------|----------|
| `PHASE_ADD` | Push new phase to `project.phases`, re-sort |
| `PHASE_UPDATE` | Merge updates by phase id |
| `PHASE_DELETE` | Remove phase; set `phaseId = null` on all objects across all floors that reference it |
| `PHASE_REORDER` | Update order values, re-sort |

The `PHASE_DELETE` cascade iterates all floors and all object arrays (walls, doors, windows, columns, beams, slabs, stairs, landings, fixtures, rooms, railings) to nullify orphaned `phaseId` references. Pattern follows `FLOOR_DELETE` cascade.

### `src/app/EditorProvider.jsx`
New state fields in `createInitialEditorState`:
```js
activePhaseId: null,        // selected phase for viewing/assigning
phaseViewMode: 'all',       // 'all' | 'single' | 'cumulative'
```

New reducer actions:
- `SET_ACTIVE_PHASE` → sets `activePhaseId`
- `SET_PHASE_VIEW_MODE` → sets `phaseViewMode`

Add `useEffect` to sync `activePhaseId` when project phases change (similar to `activeFloorId` sync with `availableFloorIds`). Pass `availablePhaseIds` as a prop.

